body:
@jreback for the main reason to consider this for 0.24.1 is that there is no change in default behaviour. 
It is true we are adding new behaviour (behind the new keyword `sort`), which ideally can live in master a bit longer. 
An alternative would be to only change the default of `sort=True` to `sort=None` here for 0.24.1, and add the new behaviour of always sorting for `sort=True` in master / for 0.25. But then the question is: what to do with `sort=True` in 0.24.1? IMO we should then disallow it (eg raise a NotImplementedError), which basically means postponing the `sort=True` to 0.25.0 (with `sort=None` as the current default of sometimes sorting still available in 0.24.1 of course). Which also feels a bit stupid to me, hence why I am in favor of doing this for 0.24.1.
